title: Prince Harry met up with ex-girlfriend Chelsy Davy during three-month conservation projects in Africa
text:
Prince Harry met up with ex-girlfriend Chelsy Davy during three-month conservation projects in Africa 
Prince Harry and Chelsy Davy broke up shortly after Kate Middleton and Prince William’s wedding back in April 2011.

Prince Harry and Chelsy Davy broke up shortly after Kate Middleton and Prince William’s wedding back in April 2011. 
But according to The Sun , the Zimbabwe beauty and the royal bachelor secretly met up last month and the two are thinking of giving their relationship another chance. 
“Harry still holds a candle for her. Chelsy has his heart,” a friend told the publication. “They saw each other recently. There’s still very much something between them.” 
“He has never fallen out of love with Chelsy. She’s not like other girls; she’s strong, independent and a rule-breaker. She does everything on her own terms,” a source added. 
Harry and Chelsy met in 2004, and they were in an on-and-off relationship until 2011 when the pair split up after Kate and William’s nuptials. 
Princess Eugenie, William and Harry’s cousin, introduced him to Cressida Bonas but the couple separated in April 2014. Chelsy Davy and her ex-boyfriend, jeweler Charles Goode, parted ways in January. 
Reports of Prince Harry planning to meet Chelsy Davy during his conservation trip in Africa appeared in June when Vanity Fair reported that the two have stayed in touch and that they are planning to see each other there. Spread the rumor
